🌐 VPC ----------------------------
  📍 VPC (Virtual Private Cloud) → A global private network in Google Cloud Platform where all your resources communicate securely.
  📍Subnet → A regional IP range inside a VPC used to group resources (e.g., 10.0.1.0/24 in asia-south1).
  📍Internal IP → Private IP used for communication between resources within the VPC (e.g., web → DB).
  📍External IP → Public IP used to access resources from the internet (e.g., users hitting a web server).
  📍Firewall Rules → Allow/deny traffic based on IP, port, and protocol (e.g., allow port 80 from internet).
  📍Routes → Define where network traffic should go (e.g., default route sends traffic to internet).
  📍Internet Gateway (implicit) → Enables outbound/inbound internet access without manual setup.
  📍VPC Peering → Private connection between two VPCs (e.g., dev VPC ↔ prod VPC).
  📍Shared VPC → Central VPC shared across multiple projects for better control.
  📍Private Google Access → Lets VMs access GCP services without needing external IPs.

